## Core Design Rules

### Colors
- Generate full 10-shade palette (50–950) using HSL-based generation
- Primary → shade-500 = base color, shades derive from HSL adjustments
- Always include semantic colors: success (#10B981), warning (#F59E0B), error (#EF4444), info (#3B82F6)
- Neutrals: tint with 3–5% of primary hue for brand cohesion
- Never hardcode hex values in component styles — use CSS custom properties

### Typography
- Scale: 12/14/16/18/20/24/30/36/48px
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 body text (WCAG AA), 3:1 large text
- Font pairings by mood: Professional → Inter; Bold → Montserrat/Space Grotesk; Playful → Nunito/Poppins; Premium → Playfair Display/Inter

### Spacing
- 8px base grid: 4/8/12/16/24/32/48/64/80/96px scale
- Card padding: 24px (default), 16px (compact)
- Use spacing tokens, never arbitrary values

### Components
Always include all states: default, hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error

### Dark Mode
Include dark mode for every color token:
```css
:root { --color-background: #ffffff; }
[data-theme="dark"] { --color-background: #0f172a; }
```
Or `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {}` for system-preference mode.

### Motion
- Micro: 100–150ms, ease-out
- Standard: 200–300ms, ease-in-out
- Complex: 400–500ms, cubic-bezier
- Always include `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { * { animation: none !important; } }`

### Accessibility
- WCAG AA minimum for all interactive elements
- Visible focus styles (`:focus-visible` with 2px outline + offset)
- All form fields need associated `<label>`
- Images need descriptive alt text
- Interactive elements need 44×44px minimum touch target

## Token Architecture (3-Tier)

```css
/* Tier 1: Primitive values */
--primitive-blue-500: #3b82f6;

/* Tier 2: Semantic aliases */
--color-action: var(--primitive-blue-500);

/* Tier 3: Component tokens */
--button-background: var(--color-action);
```

Always build from Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3. Components reference Tier 3. Themes only need to override Tier 2.

## HTML Email Rules (when working on email)
- Use `<table>` layout for Outlook compatibility
- Inline all styles (no `<link>` stylesheets)
- VML bulletproof buttons for Outlook
- Max width 600px, min font-size 14px
- Include preheader text (hidden, 85–100 chars)

## Social Media Specs (when creating social content)
- Instagram Feed: 1080×1080px (square) or 1080×1350px (portrait)
- Instagram Story/Reel: 1080×1920px (safe zone: 1080×1420px center)
- LinkedIn: 1200×628px (feed), 1080×1080px (square)
- TikTok: 1080×1920px (safe zone: 1080×1200px center)
- Twitter/X: 1600×900px

## Framework Conventions (when generating code)
- **React + Tailwind**: TypeScript, `cn()` utility, named exports
- **Next.js**: Use `'use client'` only when needed, prefer Server Components
- **Vue 3**: Composition API with `<script setup>`, TypeScript
- **Svelte 5**: Use runes (`$state`, `$derived`)
- **Astro**: Islands architecture, `.astro` components with framework islands
